    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><p><i>6th-level Circle of the Stars feature</i></p><p>Whenever you finish a long rest, you can consult your Star Map for omens. When you do so, roll a die. Until you finish your next long rest, you gain access to a special reaction based on whether you rolled an even or an odd number on the die:</p><ul class=\"rd__list rd__list-hang-notitle\"><li class=\"rd__li \"><p class=\"rd__p-list-item\" data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Weal (even)\"><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Weal (even).</span> Whenever a creature you can see within 30 feet of you is about to make an attack roll, a saving throw, or an ability check, you can use your reaction to roll a [[/r d6]] and add the number rolled to the total.</p></li><li class=\"rd__li \"><p class=\"rd__p-list-item\" data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Woe (odd)\"><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Woe (odd).</span> Whenever a creature you can see within 30 feet of you is about to make an attack roll, a saving throw, or an ability check, you can use your reaction to roll a [[/r d6]] and subtract the number rolled from the total.</p></li></ul><p>You can use this reaction a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p></div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
